<title type="html"><![CDATA[09/18(Sat.)Taiwan promoting bilingual by 2030 .../Paddling and spa pools...reopen with restrictions in Taiwan(Ellen)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=542&amp;p=565#p565"><![CDATA[
09/18(Sat.) Taiwan to set up agency promoting bilingual by 2030 initiative/Paddling and spa pools, public showers, reopen with restrictions in Taiwan(Ellen)<br /><br /><span style="color: #FF0000">There is no on-site meeting during the pandemic of COVID-19.<br /><br />加入 Zoom 會議<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ... NKSU5MQT09<br /><br />會議 ID：929 8726 6213<br />密碼：112233<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:10 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:10-7:40 pm Session 1 Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Presentation 1<br />8:00-8:10 pm Break<br />8:10-8:40: Session 2 Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Presentation 2<br /><br />At the presentation, the time limit is 1-2 minutes for each speaker.</span><br />-----------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Article 1: Taiwan to set up agency promoting bilingual by 2030 initiative</span><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/4280848">https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/4280848</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1. What are the reasons that you think Taiwan people learned English from elementary schools or high schools for many years, but still can’t communicate with foreigners fluently?  <br />2. Do you agree with the policy of “Taiwan to set up agency promoting bilingual by 2030”? Why or why not? <br />3. Do you have any good suggestion of helping promote English from the education? Can you share with us?<br />4. Recall how you learned English; do you think your way/method is good/efficient? Can you share your experience? <br />----------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Article 2: Paddling and spa pools, public showers, reopen with restrictions in Taiwan</span><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/4280725">https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/4280725</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1. What kinds of sports are difficult to do during the Covid-19 pandemic? Please discuss it with your group members?<br />2. Do you do the exercise during the Covid-19 pandemic? What kinds of sports do you do? Is it convenience to do the exercise during that period? How do you overcome it?<br />3. Are you a swimming-lover? How do you think the restrictions of the article? Will it cause any inconvenience to you if you are the swimmer? <br />4. Since it’s alert level 2 now, there are a lot of places reopen (such like zoo, amusement park, restaurants…), will you go these places after it reopen? Why or why not? <br />5. Have you got the vaccine? Why or why now? If you’re vaccinated, please share your side effects or any uncomfortable feeling with your group members.  <br />  <br /><span style="color: #0000FF">P.S.<br />1.參加三次後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放與熱情來參加自由的全英文會話聚會~</span><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=12531">Danny Lin</a> — Mon Sep 13, 2021 9:39 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
